    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for taking the time to share your comments and we are very sorry to learn of your unsatisfactory experience on the Postnatal Ward after you gave birth. 

As this falls short of the care and service we expect our patients to receive, we would like to apologise and hope we can assure you that the Trust strives to provide patients with excellent care so we are sorry we did not achieved it for you on this occasion. 

Your review and experience has been forwarded to the Senior Management team and the Ward Manager who will be raising everything in your review at their next team meeting. The Senior Management Team will also be liasing with the Manager and Lead Midwife of the Postnatal Ward for assurance this has been raised and discussed.

We again appreciate your comments as all patient/service userâ€™s comments enable us to monitor and improve our services where required.  

Should you still remain concerned about your experience, please contact our Patient Advice and Liaison Service (PALS) at your earliest opportunity on telephone 0161 604 5897, or email pals@pat.nhs.uk quoting that you have been advised to do so via NHS Website, so we can discuss and address your experience.

Kind regards
The Patient Experience Team.
